42, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hercules Furens” 756. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> with <i>accusative</i>, πόλεμον τολμήσαντα <b>undertaking, venturing on</b> it, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 8.519; [ἐσόδους] τετόλμακε 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 5.117 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; τ. πάντα, δεινά, ἔργον αἴσχιστον, etc., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 761, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Iphigenia Aulidensis” 133 (_anapaest meter_), “Med.” 695, etc.; ὦ πᾶν σὺ τολμήσασα καὶ πέρα 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 189; also τ. τὰ βέλτιστα 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 3.56, 4.98; πικρὰν πεῖραν 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 471 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; see at {τόλμημα}:—hence in <i>passive</i>, ο ἐτολμήθη πατήρ such things as my father <b>had dared</b> (or <b>done</b>) <b>against him,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Electra” 277 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τοῦτο τετολμήσθω εἰπεῖν <b>let us take courage</b> to say this, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 503b; τὰ τολμηθέντα 1st c.AD: Josephus Historicus “Antiquitates Judaicae” 2.3.1; αἱ τετολμημέναι ἐπίνοιαι 1st c.AD: Philo Judaeus 1.674; τὰ τετ. εἰς ἐμέ “PGoodsp.Cair.” 15.3 (4th c.AD). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.4</b></Level3> so in <i>active</i>, τετολμηκυῖαι [λέξεις] <b>daring</b> expressions, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Philodemus Gadarensis Epigrammaticus “Rh.” 1.341 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G5111","accentedUnicode":"τολμάω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0662","matchingForm":"ἀποτολμάω","stepTransliteration":"apotolmaō","gloss":"be bold","_zh_tw_Gloss":"放膽","_es_Gloss":"atreverse","_zh_Gloss":"放胆"},{"strongNumber":"G3954","matchingForm":"παρρησία","stepTransliteration":"parrēsia","gloss":